Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}.

Stir @marinara sauce{14%ounce}, @milk{6.75%ounce}, and @butter{1%tablespoon} into pan. Bring to a boil, then stir in as many @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like and half the @spinach{5%ounce}. Cook, stirring, until spinach wilts, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If you want more veggies, stir in all the spinach.

Stir drained penne into sauce. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Evenly sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{½%cup} and @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}. Top with a large drizzle of olive oil.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a #baking dish{}.

Bake penne mixture until panko is browned and crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}. Divide between plates and serve.